def: A maker of catalogues; esp. one skilled in the making ofcatalogues.
Showing blushes; rosy red; having a warm and delicate colorlike some roses and other flowers; blooming; ruddy; roseate.The dappled pink and blushing rose. Prior.

A peptonelike body, insoluble in alcohol, formed by boilingcollagen or gelatin for a long time in water. Hemicollin, a likebody, is also formed at the same time, and differs from semiglutin bybeing partly soluble in alcohol.
So as to be measurable by quantity; quantitatively.
Money paid at fairs for leave to break ground for booths.Ainsworth.
Like, or allied to, the porcupines; -- said of a group(Hystricomorpha) of rodents.
A fragrant substance which is the chief constituent ofambergris.
A gigantic extinct herbivorous mammal from South America,having teeth bent like a bow. It is the type of the order Toxodonta.
The quality or condition of being imperfect; want ofperfection; incompleteness; deficiency; fault or blemish.Sent to my account With all my imperfections on my head. Shak.
To weigh or consider beforehand; to premeditate. [Obs.]Spenser. Sir T. Elyot.
